# Tailwind Dark Mode Enforcement

## Purpose
- Ensure the template renders in dark mode by default across all labs.
- Fixes: TEST â†’ Tailwind template not in dark mode (while app and vuln function correctly).

## Requirements
- Tailwind config must enable dark mode via class:

```javascript
// tailwind.config.js
module.exports = {
  darkMode: "class",
  content: ["./**/*.php", "./**/*.html", "./**/*.js"],
  theme: { extend: {} },
  plugins: []
};
```

- Base HTML must enable dark by default:

```html
<!doctype html>
<html class="dark" lang="en">
```

- Use dark classes in the body as a baseline:

```html
<body class="min-h-screen bg-black text-white">
```

## Validation
- Check that `darkMode: "class"` is present in `tailwind.config.js` (or inline CDN config).
- Ensure the root `<html>` tag includes `class="dark"` so dark styles are active by default.
- Visual check: background is black and text is white across pages.

